args: And you're certain a fiend slipped into the\ncastle courtyard last night, Cleo?
Absolutely. I awoke this morning to find\nthe Sweet Retreat nibbled to bits.
Hmm. It's curious that no one noticed.
The culprit is clearly quite clever.
We'll need someone in disguise to keep\nwatch.
Might I ask your help in this, Elisanne?
Of course. I promise to see your candy\nthief brought to swift justice.
Ah ha! Shown yourself already, have you,\nfiend?!
Ah! I beg your pardon, Your Highness...\nBut may I ask what brings you here at this\nlate hour?
I heard you were keeping watch all by\nyourself, and thought I'd drop by to see\nhow things were going.
Worry not, Highness. This is my station,\nand I have things well in hand.
But I do thank you for your kind concern.\nYou always—
Hmm? What was that noise?\nLeaves in the wind, maybe?
...No. It moves at a steady pace.
And it makes for the Sweet Retreat.
This may be our fiend. Let's follow it.
Shall we split up? A pincer attack will\nensure it has nowhere to run.
Yes, but that also doubles our chance of\nbeing heard. We should stick together.
...Er, {player_name}? Might you\ngive me a bit more space, please?
Oh, sorry! I figured we'd be less likely to\ntip off the fiend if we were close.
Walking side by side would make us twice\nas easy to spot.
Er...that may be so, but I also don't think\nwalking one atop the other is a good idea.
Elisanne? What's wrong? If you rush in,\nyou'll just—
I-it's a preemptive strike! We'll just slay\nthe creature before it sees us coming!
...Er, why are you holding a hunk of\ncookie-dough spackle?
You're the candy thief!\n*sigh* Of course you are.
Now hold on a sec! There's a reasonable\nexplanation to all'a this!
The thought'a fiends sneakin' into the\nHalidom had me walkin' the floors at\nnight, yeah?
So I decided to go on watch duty—and ya\nknow how stakeouts make a guy hungry.
Then my patrol just HAPPENS to take me\npast a house made'a treats? C'mon!\nHow am I NOT supposed to eat it?!
That is EXACTLY what you were supposed\nto do. You're no better than an animal.\nNo, a fiend!
I'll have you know your antics put me in\nan extremely uncomfortable position!
But YOU, Ranzal—you should very MUCH\nmind! I want you to think long and hard\nabout what you've done. Understood?!
